  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.13.0\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nGood Afternoon:\r\n\r\nThe HardHat plugin in Remix IDE is missing by default (version of Remix IDE - 0.31.2, version of Remixd - 0.6.12,\r\noperating system - Windows 10)\r\nThere instruction that can be found here:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/remix-ide/blob/master/docs/hardhat.md\r\nis unexact and unclear, because the concrete examples of the instalation and run in different operation systems \r\nwith concrete folders (Windows 10, MacOs, Ubuntu) are missing. So I tried to do the following:\r\n`npm install -g @remix-project/remixd`\r\n`remixd -s D:\\IDE\\VS\\Sol_tests --remix-ide https://remix.ethereum.org`\r\nHere I chose the folder with **hardhat.config.js** file, but not a folder where Remix IDE has been installed. \r\nMay be it is necessary to install HardHat to the directory where Remix IDE is installed, I don't  know.\r\nOr may be it it necessary to install Hardhat and hardhat.config. js to the C:\\Windows\\System32 directory.\r\nNothing about it is written in the file:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/remix-ide/blob/master/docs/hardhat.md.\r\nThen I opened a new terminal in **D:\\IDE\\VS\\Sol_tests** and finally ran the following command:\r\n`npx hardhat node`\r\nBut whet I tried to connect to localhost using Remix IDE I go the following error:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42437106/224665315-adfbe3a5-390a-47a2-af2b-b14fee96f063.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n`npm install -g @remix-project/remixd`\r\n`remixd -s D:\\IDE\\VS\\Sol_tests --remix-ide https://remix.ethereum.org`\r\nAnd then in a new terminal you should run\r\n`npx hardhat node`\r\nAnd finally run Remix IDE.\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\n_No response_",
